text: Renie Cox (born September 15, 1938) is a retired American alpine ski racer and a former member of the United States Ski Team. She competed in the slalom at the 1960 Winter Olympics and finished ninth. Born in Lowville, New York, Cox was raised in the Lake Placid area and attended the University of Denver in Colorado.
